<TITLE> BJSC recommends recruiting 210 judges </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 28 (bdnews24.com) Bangladesh Judicial Service Commission (BJSC) has recommended recruiting 210 judges, the government said in a statement Sunday. The process of hiring is expected to begin soon, according to the statement. BJSC chairman Justice MM Ruhul Amin mentioned the recommendation in the commission's annual report submitted to President Iajuddin Ahmed Sunday. Iajuddin asked the commission to take utmost care while recruiting eligible, meritorious and promising people as assistant judges. Iajuddin underscored proper training for the judges to ensure their professional skills. bdne
